2 Objective
***********

* Menu:

* STREAMS Packages::		STREAMS packages in the master package
* Other Packages::		Other packages in the master package

The "OpenSS7 Master Package" package is intended as a common build and
installation package for all other packages available from The OpenSS7 Project
(http://www.openss7.org/).  The master package began as a slim framework for
development of the other packages and blossomed into a combined build and
development environment for all OpenSS7 packages.  The master package is
currently very mature and provides a simple way for users of the OpenSS7
packages to download, build and install all available OpenSS7 Project packages
without concern or consideration for intricate dependencies between packages.


File: openss7.info,  Node: STREAMS Packages,  Next: Other Packages,  Up: Objective

2.1 STREAMS Packages
====================

Because OpenSS7 packages first built with "Linux STREAMS (LiS)" but now build
with the superior "Linux Fast-STREAMS (LfS)", the master package had the
objective from the onset of being able to build all OpenSS7 packages against
either "LiS" or "LfS" or both.  This was the case from "LiS" version _2.18.1_
through _2.18.3_ and "streams" version _0.7a.3_ through _0.7a.5_, or master
package releases _0.9.2.A_ through _0.9.2.C_.  With the release of master
package _0.9.2.D_ containing "streams" _0.7a.6_, "LiS" is no longer supported
in the master package.  The contained "LiS" _2.18.4_ is the final release of
"LiS" from the OpenSS7 Project.


File: openss7.info,  Node: Other Packages,  Prev: STREAMS Packages,  Up: Objective

2.2 Other Packages
==================

The other packages in the OpenSS7 Master Package normally depend upon one of
the "STREAMS" packages and zero or more of the other sub-packages in the master
package.  The OpenSS7 Master Package, by default, builds `Linux Fast-STREAMS'
(`streams-0.7a.6.rc3') and all other packages against `Linux Fast-STREAMS'.  It
is possible; however, to direct the package to build against `Linux STREAMS'
(`LiS-2.18.4.rc3'), or both `LiS' and `LfS' (such as is done to release the
master package).


